<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="100" pageId="3" pageNumber="99" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1549,2023]" lastBlockId="4.[151,1436,152,695]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="100" pageId="3" pageNumber="99">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,539,1549,1572]" pageId="3" pageNumber="99">Diagnosis and Description.</emphasis>
Wingspan 
<quantity box="[677,807,1549,1572]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.7" metricValueMax="3.8" metricValueMin="3.6" pageId="3" pageNumber="99" unit="mm" value="37.0" valueMax="38.0" valueMin="36.0">36–38 mm</quantity>
. The new species with its prominent morphological autapomorphies represents a unique lineage within the entire Holarctic genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1818" box="[983,1050,1584,1607]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Xestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="99" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="lato">
<emphasis box="[983,1050,1584,1607]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="99">Xestia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1057,1095,1584,1607]" pageId="3" pageNumber="99" sensu="lato">s. l.</taxonomicNameLabel>
Externally it slightly resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Boursin, 1954" authorityName="Boursin" authorityYear="1954" box="[151,512,1618,1642]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Rhyacia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="99" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mirabilis">
<emphasis box="[151,349,1618,1642]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="99">Rhyacia mirabilis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Boursin, Ch." box="[356,512,1619,1642]" pageId="3" pageNumber="99" pagination="213 - 303" refId="ref2054" refString="Boursin, Ch. (1954) Die &quot; Agrotis &quot; - Arten aus Dr. h. c. H. Hone's China-Ausbeuten. Bonner Zoologische Beitrage, 5, 213 - 303." type="journal article" year="1954">Boursin, 1954</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Gyulai &amp; Ronkay, 2001" authorityName="Gyulai &amp; Ronkay" authorityYear="2001" box="[569,996,1618,1642]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Rhyacia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="99" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="admiranda">
<emphasis box="[569,720,1618,1642]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="99">R. admiranda</emphasis>
Gyulai &amp; Ronkay, 2001
</taxonomicName>
, but has a less robust body and broader trigonical forewings with a short apex and straight outer margin. The dark bluish-ashy grey forewing ground colour distinguishes it from the two bright greenish 
<taxonomicName box="[644,822,1687,1711]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Rhyacia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="99" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[644,733,1687,1711]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="99">Rhyacia</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
; the orbicular and reniform stigmata are lighter than the ground colour, but not so dark as those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Boursin" authorityYear="1954" box="[603,729,1722,1746]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Rhyacia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="99" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mirabilis">
<emphasis box="[603,729,1722,1746]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="99">R. mirabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gyulai &amp; Ronkay" authorityYear="2001" box="[782,929,1722,1746]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Rhyacia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="99" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="admiranda">
<emphasis box="[782,929,1722,1746]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="99">R. admiranda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gyulai &amp; Ronkay &amp; Saldaitis" authorityYear="2013" box="[943,1077,1723,1746]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Xestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="99" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rimas">
<emphasis box="[943,1077,1723,1746]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="99">Xestia rimas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1092,1156,1723,1746]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–5" captionStartId="1.[151,269,1880,1903]" captionTargetBox="[152,1435,194,1856]" captionTargetId="figure-92@1.[151,1436,194,1856]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–5. Xestia ssp. adults. 1. X. elisabetha sp. n., male, holotype, China, Sichuan (coll. P. Gyulai); 2. X. elisabetha sp. n., male, paratype, China, Sichuan (coll. P. Gyulai); 3. X. aplectoides, male, China, Yunnan (coll. P. Gyulai); 4. X. rimas sp. n., male, holotype, China, Sichuan (coll. P. Gyulai); 5. Mixed forest – the biotope of X. rimas sp. n., China, N-Sichuan, road Songpan/Jiuzhaigou." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5268857" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5268857/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="99">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
) is also somewhat similar to certain other Holarctic larger, greyish coloured members of the subgenus 
<taxonomicName authority="Guenee, 1852" authorityName="Guenee" authorityYear="1852" box="[1030,1319,1756,1780]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Pachnobia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="99" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1030,1152,1756,1780]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="99">Pachnobia</emphasis>
Guenée, 1852
</taxonomicName>
(formerly 
<taxonomicName authority="Staudinger, 1871" authorityName="Staudinger" authorityYear="1871" box="[151,468,1792,1815]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Anomogyna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="99" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,278,1792,1815]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="99">Anomogyna</emphasis>
Staudinger, 1871
</taxonomicName>
; was synonymised with 
<taxonomicName authority=", Lafontaine, 1998" authorityName=", Lafontaine" authorityYear="1998" box="[727,1039,1791,1815]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Pachnobia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="99" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[727,843,1791,1815]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="99">Pachnobia</emphasis>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Lafontaine, J. D." box="[856,1039,1792,1815]" pageId="3" pageNumber="99" refId="ref2525" refString="Lafontaine, J. D. (1998) The Moths of America North of Mexico - 27.3 Noctuoidea, Noctuidae (part.). The Wedge Entomological Research Foundation, Washington, D. C., 348 pp., 8 colour pls, 36 monochrome pls, 124 maps." type="book" year="1998">Lafontaine, 1998</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
) but is easily separable by the almost unicolorous dark bluish ashy grey forewing ground colour, the unusual light ochreous suffusion of the basal field, the large, regular, light ochreous-grey filled orbicular stigma and the conspicuous small, dark ochreous spot in the indistinct, darkened reniform stigma. Antennae filiform; legs blackish; hindlegs with a single long and two shorter spines; head, thoracic pubescence and palpi light ashy grey; palpi with black underside; abdomen light brown; antemedial line double, wavy; postmedial line simple, arcuate and serrated; both crosslines diffuse, blackish-grey; subterminal line obsolescent, with blackish trigonical costal patch and black arrowheads at inner side; hindwing brownish-grey, with darker cellular discal spot and wavy medial line; cilia of both wings ashy grey. The male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[1096,1230,152,175]" captionStart="FIGURES 12–15" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1411,1434]" captionTargetBox="[176,1410,441,1391]" captionTargetId="figure-384@3.[167,1417,430,1397]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 12–15. Xestia ssp. males genitalia. 12. X. rimas sp. n., holotype, capsule, prep. PGy3213; 13. X. rimas sp. n., holotype, aedeagus, prep. PGy3213; 14. X. rimas sp. n., paratype, capsule, prep. PGy2893; 15. X. rimas sp. n., paratype, aedeagus, prep. PGy2893." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5268863" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5268863/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="100">Figs. 12–15</figureCitation>
) are typical of the subgenus 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Lafontaine" authorityYear="1998" box="[257,373,185,209]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Pachnobia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="100" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[257,373,185,209]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="100">Pachnobia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but the distal part of the valva is more elongated, terminally bifurcate, and resembles those of some species of the subgenus 
<taxonomicName authority="Alpheraky, 1892" authorityName="Alpheraky" authorityYear="1892" box="[429,711,220,244]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Raddea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="100" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[429,514,220,244]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="100">Raddea</emphasis>
Alpheraky, 1892
</taxonomicName>
(formerly 
<taxonomicName authority="Boursin, 1963" authorityName="Boursin" authorityYear="1963" box="[837,1164,220,244]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Erebophasma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="100" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[837,992,220,244]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="100">Erebophasma</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Boursin, Ch." box="[1000,1164,221,244]" pageId="4" pageNumber="100" pagination="9 - 107" refId="ref2089" refString="Boursin, Ch. (1963) Die Noctuinae-Arten (Agrotinae vulgo sensu) aus Dr. h. c. H. Hone China-Ausbeuten. Forschungsberichte des Landes Nordrhein-Westfalen, 1170, 9 - 107. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1007 / 978 - 3 - 663 - 07024 - 5" type="journal article" year="1963">Boursin, 1963</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
; was synonymised with 
<taxonomicName authority=", Lafontaine 1998" authorityName="Lafontaine" authorityYear="1998" box="[151,422,255,279]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Raddea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="100" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,239,255,279]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="100">Raddea,</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Lafontaine, J. D." box="[246,422,256,279]" pageId="4" pageNumber="100" refId="ref2525" refString="Lafontaine, J. D. (1998) The Moths of America North of Mexico - 27.3 Noctuoidea, Noctuidae (part.). The Wedge Entomological Research Foundation, Washington, D. C., 348 pp., 8 colour pls, 36 monochrome pls, 124 maps." type="book" year="1998">Lafontaine 1998</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Kononenko, V. S. &amp; Volynkin, A. V. &amp; Matov, A. Y." box="[475,724,256,279]" pageId="4" pageNumber="100" pagination="51 - 62" refId="ref2457" refString="Kononenko, V. S., Volynkin, A. V. &amp; Matov, A. Y. (2012) A revision of the Xestia (Radddea) alexis (Kozhanchikov, 1928) speciesgroup with a checklist of subgenus Raddea Alpheraky, 1892 and description of brachipterous females (Lepidoptera, Noctuidae, Noctuinae). Zootaxa, 3590, 51 - 62." type="journal article" year="2012">Kononenko et al. 2012</bibRefCitation>
), especially 
<taxonomicName authority="(Chen, 1985)" baseAuthorityName="Chen" baseAuthorityYear="1985" box="[856,1172,255,279]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Raddea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="100" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirsuta">
<emphasis box="[856,1021,255,279]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="100">Raddea hirsuta</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Chen, Y. - X." box="[1035,1164,256,279]" pageId="4" pageNumber="100" pagination="317 - 318" refId="ref2174" refString="Chen, Y. - X. (1985) A new species of the genus Estimata Kozhanchikov (Lepidoptera: Noctuidae) Acta Entomologica Sinica, 28 (3), 317 - 318." type="journal article" year="1985">Chen, 1985</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. The specific features of the male genitalia of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gyulai &amp; Ronkay &amp; Saldaitis" authorityYear="2013" box="[374,465,290,313]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Xestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="100" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rimas">
<emphasis box="[374,465,290,313]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="100">X. rimas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are the large, broadly calyciform juxta, with deep, laterally sinuous V-shaped dorso-medial incision; particularly distally elongated, terminally asymmetrically bifurcate, pointed valva; medium-large, thick and basally strongly curved, apically acutely pointed harpe; large knot-shaped carinal plate, appearing rather like a basal cornutus; the dorsally recurved, ample vesica with sclerotised, slightly serrated subbasal plate. Female unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,152,695]" pageId="4" pageNumber="100">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,519,429,452]" pageId="4" pageNumber="100">Bionomics and Distribution.</emphasis>
The 
<specimenCount box="[574,674,429,452]" pageId="4" pageNumber="100" type="male">six males</specimenCount>
were collected at ultraviolet light on 
<date box="[1076,1213,429,452]" pageId="4" pageNumber="100" value="2011-07-23">
23 July 
<quantity box="[1161,1213,429,452]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.10794" pageId="4" pageNumber="100" unit="in" value="2011.0">2011</quantity>
</date>
in 
<collectingRegion box="[1248,1436,429,452]" country="China" name="Sichuan" pageId="4" pageNumber="100">Sichuan Province</collectingRegion>
in a remote area located at the southern end of the Minshan mountain range (
<figureCitation box="[1038,1108,464,487]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–5" captionStartId="1.[151,269,1880,1903]" captionTargetBox="[152,1435,194,1856]" captionTargetId="figure-92@1.[151,1436,194,1856]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–5. Xestia ssp. adults. 1. X. elisabetha sp. n., male, holotype, China, Sichuan (coll. P. Gyulai); 2. X. elisabetha sp. n., male, paratype, China, Sichuan (coll. P. Gyulai); 3. X. aplectoides, male, China, Yunnan (coll. P. Gyulai); 4. X. rimas sp. n., male, holotype, China, Sichuan (coll. P. Gyulai); 5. Mixed forest – the biotope of X. rimas sp. n., China, N-Sichuan, road Songpan/Jiuzhaigou." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5268857" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5268857/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="100">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). The collecting area is near Jiuzhaigou National Park. The climate in the valley is cool, with a mean annual temperature of 7.2 degrees C and total annual rainfall of 
<quantity box="[349,439,533,556]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.609999999999999" pageId="4" pageNumber="100" unit="mm" value="661.0">661 mm</quantity>
(80% of which occurs between May and October). Jiuzhaigou's ecosystem is classified as temperate broad-leaved forest and woodlands, with mixed mountain and highland systems. Among other summer noctuid species collected at the time were 
<taxonomicName authority="(Draudt, 1950)" baseAuthorityName="Draudt" baseAuthorityYear="1950" box="[614,1000,601,625]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Haderonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="100" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albirena">
<emphasis box="[614,828,601,625]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="100">Haderonia albirena</emphasis>
(Draudt, 1950)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Moore, 1867)" baseAuthorityName="Moore" baseAuthorityYear="1867" box="[1012,1431,601,625]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Diphtherocome" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="100" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallida">
<emphasis box="[1012,1264,601,625]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="100">Diphtherocome pallida</emphasis>
(Moore, 1867)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Gyulai, Ronkay &amp; Saldaitis, 2011" authorityName="Gyulai, Ronkay &amp; Saldaitis" authorityYear="2011" box="[151,712,636,660]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Xestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="100" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="morandinii">
<emphasis box="[151,342,636,660]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="100">Xestia morandinii</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Gyulai, P. &amp; Ronkay, L. &amp; Saldaitis, A." box="[349,712,637,660]" pageId="4" pageNumber="100" pagination="166 - 197" refId="ref2210" refString="Gyulai, P., Ronkay, L. &amp; Saldaitis, A. (2011) New Noctuidae species from China and the Himalayas. Esperiana, 16, 166 - 197." type="journal article" year="2011">Gyulai, Ronkay &amp; Saldaitis, 2011</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Gyulai, Ronkay &amp; Saldaitis, 2011" authorityName="Gyulai, Ronkay &amp; Saldaitis" authorityYear="2011" box="[723,1284,636,660]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Papestra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="100" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="florianii">
<emphasis box="[723,913,636,660]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="100">Papestra florianii</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Gyulai, P. &amp; Ronkay, L. &amp; Saldaitis, A." box="[920,1284,637,660]" pageId="4" pageNumber="100" pagination="166 - 197" refId="ref2210" refString="Gyulai, P., Ronkay, L. &amp; Saldaitis, A. (2011) New Noctuidae species from China and the Himalayas. Esperiana, 16, 166 - 197." type="journal article" year="2011">Gyulai, Ronkay &amp; Saldaitis, 2011</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
